The paper deals with finding acyclic graphs, which is a problem related to graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes several encodings of the problem and compares them using state-of-the-art SAT solvers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem of finding acyclic graphs can also be seen as a constraint satisfaction problem, which makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves propositional formulas and models, which are concepts related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
